ownedComment.body:
WAN Protocols operate at the lowest three levels of the OSI model (i.e., physical, data link, and network) and are used to define communications over different types of wide-area media.
The SID model defines ATM, FrameRelay, HDLC, ISDN, PPP, SLIP, SMDS, and X.25 as examples of subclasses of this class.
